When I bought this, I was looking for a reasonably priced copy of "Lust in the Dust".  When I saw this combo, I thought that I would take a chance, buy it, and pray for the best on the movie "Beyond Therapy".  That was a major mistake!  "Beyond Therapy" is a homophobe's dream movie with so many horrible cliches that it is sickening!  I will avoid watching it.  As for "Lust in the Dust", well what can I say?  C'mon, a movie with Divine, Tab Hunter, and Rita Moreno!  How can you go wrong?  But...having said that, if you can't afford the $25-$35 price range that some sellers are charging, get this.  Otherwise, do as I sometimes do and don't buy it and pray that the price will eventually go down.

I got this two movie disc for Lust In The Dust as it was cheaper this way than on it's own.  This is an excellent western comedy that should give most people a few good laughs.  Beyond Therapy I tried but couldn't find anything funny about it.  For me this is still a good buy.

Lust in the Dust deserves a one-star rating, and for a one-star movie, it deserves five stars. This film is so utterly zany.  It is too long and is slow at times, but has some great moments -- Margarita's dirge upon the death of her (boyfriend?) Bernardo; Rosie's accidental killing of her bedmates, the final shoot-out between the sisters, and Rosie's singing audition.  The costume designer who came up with the dresses for these "ladies" deserves a lot of credit.  Divine is wonderful and LanIe Kazan steals the scenes every time.  My favorite lines in the film:  "Rosie, don't you think you've had enough?"  "I know when I've had enough, I fall on the floor." And:  "You could eat off these floors, and you probably will!"
